BRUSSELS Club Brugge coach Ivan Leko, whose team is playing in the Champions League, was one of several Belgian football figures arrested on Wednesday, a source close to the investigation said. The headquarters of Club Brugge, Standard Liege, Anderlecht and KRC Genk, the current leader of the Belgian Premier League, were searched in the operation, the source said, confirming information from the Belgian media.   Federal prosecutors told AFP that a well-known football agent had been arrested in his home.